[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm thinking about how the handler casts args[0] to RelNode, which means I could pass any instance that implements RelNode. I'm reflecting on whether a dynamic proxy would work directly here. The custom `AbstractRelNode` seems to require a cluster, so that complicates things. The RelNode interface has many methods, but currently, the logical values look okay. I wonder if `rel.getClass()` returning LogicalValues might lead to issues since the provider was ignored, and that’s something to watch out for.
